post_text:
**RESCHEDULED**
Good evening Argosy families and scholars,
As many of you may already know, there will be peaceful protesting throughout the city of Fall River on Saturday, June 6th. As an organization, we feel it is appropriate to reschedule the End of Year Parade we had scheduled during that time. The new date for the End of Year Parade will be Saturday, June 13th from 2pm-3pm!
If you choose to participate in the peaceful protesting this weekend to support the cause, please be extremely careful, safe and stay together! #blacklivesmatter #saytheirnames #takeastand #supportoneanother #argosyinmotion

post_text:
#blackout
Dear Argosy Collegiate families,
During today's virtual staff meeting, Argosy Collegiate staff observed a moment of silence honoring the life of George Floyd, an African American man who was needlessly killed in Minneapolis last week. Argosy Collegiate stands with the Massachusetts Charter Public School Association in taking a stand against systemic racism.
The life of George Floyd, in addition to the lives of so many other Black Americans who have needlessly left this world far too soon, reinforces the importance of strong public education that focuses on fostering empathetic, compassionate, hard-working individuals that embrace diversity.
If you or your child need support during these troubling times, our school adjustment counselors and school psychologists are available. #BlackLivesMatter #SayTheirNames #EnoughIsEnough

post_text:
Nurse Kelly, ACCS Health and Wellness Coordinator, shows how easily germs can spread even when you think you are being safe.

https://youtu.be/kPyJh9f2oS8

Her message is to stay home if you can or as much as you can, avoid touching your face, cover your nose and mouth if you do have to go out, and to wash/sanitize your hands every chance you can. Only WE can stop the spread! #argosyinmotion #argosyovercovid #education #healthandwellness #stayhome #alonetogether #stopthespread

post_text:
#dreamchallenge Week 2 #RESPECT
Good evening Argosy Community!
I hope that everyone is safe, healthy and staying positive as we continue to push through this pandemic!
This week, the Dean Team challenges you to demonstrate an act of Respect! Respect means to show awareness or concern for the feelings, wishes, rights and traditions of others (dictionary.com). We can show respect through our words and actions to others, to ourselves, to our classwork, to the environment and to the world. We encourage ALL scholars to participate by capturing this act of RESPECT by taking a picture or making a video! Please send your picture or video to mchoice@argosycollegiate.org. Remember, your picture or video could potentially make it on our Argosy Facebook and Instagram pages!
Good luck!
Mr. Choice
#deanteamchallenge #showrespect #dreamvalues
#argosycollegiatecharterschool #masscharterschools #education #middleschool #highschool #argosyovercorona #schoolcommunity

post_text:
Dear Argosy Community,

I hope you and your families are doing well and staying healthy during COVID-19!

On behalf of the Dean Team, we are challenging you to demonstrate acts of our DREAM values during your quarantine! Each week, we will focus on one of our DREAM values. For this week, we challenge you to share a picture, or a video of you demonstrating DETERMINATION! Please get creative and have fun during this challenge! Keep in mind that we are practicing social distancing, so we encourage you to be mindful of that when demonstrating these acts! Also, we expect ALL scholars to act mature and appropriately if you choose to make a video! That includes language, the background of your picture or video, know your audience! I ask that you send your photos or videos to my email at mchoice@argosycollegiate.org. If you have trouble send your picture or video, please let me know and i'll troubleshoot with you! Your picture or video could end up on our Argosy social media pages (Facebook, Instagram)!

Good luck!
text:
Dear Argosy Community,

I hope you and your families are doing well and staying healthy during COVID-19!

On behalf of the Dean Team, we are challenging you to demonstrate acts of our DREAM values during your quarantine! Each week, we will focus on one of our DREAM values. For this week, we challenge you to share a picture, or a video of you demonstrating DETERMINATION! Please get creative and have fun during this challenge! Keep in mind that we are practicing social distancing, so we encourage you to be mindful of that when demonstrating these acts! Also, we expect ALL scholars to act mature and appropriately if you choose to make a video! That includes language, the background of your picture or video, know your audience! I ask that you send your photos or videos to my email at mchoice@argosycollegiate.org. If you have trouble send your picture or video, please let me know and i'll troubleshoot with you! Your picture or video could end up on our Argosy social media pages (Facebook, Instagram)!

Good luck!

post_text: Good and bad news on the high school basketball front against Codman Charter in Dorchester. The high school boys fought through a tough game but didn’t take the W tonight. The girls on the other hand, pulled off a W by 1 point! Shout out to Jazz K for her points scored!! Congrats #argosy! Games well played. On to the next 👌🏼#argosycollegiatecharterschool #highschool #basketball #teamwork #teamworkmakesthedreamwork
